Treatment of recurrent malignant gliomas with chronic oral high-dose tamoxifen. The present clinical trial was undertaken to assess the clinical safety and possible efficacy of administering tamoxifen to patients with recurrent malignant glial tumors at dosages calculated to achieve levels sufficient to inhibit protein kinase C within the tumor cells. Chronic p.o. tamoxifen was administered in very high dosages to 32 patients (20 males and 12 females age range, 26-75 years